      <bioghist id="aspace_eb8c69244747cb2286cf9e483f3bda1a">
         <head>Biographical Note</head>
         <p>An educator, writer, and critic, Leary taught at Duke and Columbia Universities, and the
            University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_293bb865fd6bbb2356fd2019360624e2">
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         <p>Chiefly notes, lectures, addresses, and articles on American writers, with an emphasis
            on early American literature, especially minor authors. Includes research materials on
            Philip Freneau, Parson Weems, and Henry D. Thoreau. The collection also contains
            correspondence, 1958-1985, and an autobiographical sketch by Leary. Most of this
            material is described in the container list.</p>
      </scopecontent>
